
[1]injustice

   INJUS'TICE, n. [L. injustitia; in and justitia,justice.]

   1. Iniquity; wrong; any violation of another's rights, as fraud in
   contracts, or the withholding of what is due. It has a particular
   reference to an unequal distribution of rights, property or privileges
   among persons who have equal claims.

   2. The withholding from another merited praise, or ascribing to him
   unmerited blame.
